changeHpRate.Wiki: Positive values deplete, negative values restore.\nCan scale with attributes.

changeHpPoint.Wiki: Positive values deplete, negative values restore.\nCan scale with attributes.

changeMpRate.Wiki: Positive values deplete, negative values restore.

changeMpPoint.Wiki: Positive values deplete, negative values restore.

changeStaminaRate.Wiki: Positive values deplete, negative values restore.

changeStaminaPoint.Wiki: Positive values deplete, negative values restore.

staminaRecoverChangeSpeed.Wiki: Adds or subtracts value from base stamina regen.

insideDurability.Wiki: Requires State Info 4\nPositive values deplete, negative values restore.

maxDurability.Wiki: Affects the hits required to damage equipment.

soulRate.Wiki: Requires State Info 76\nMultiplier for souls received.

soul.Wiki: Directly adds or subtracts value of souls.

animIdOffset.Wiki: Used to change NPC movesets (i.e. sword hollow to spear hollow).

haveSoulRate.Wiki: Multiplier to the amount of souls the affected drops

targetPriority.Wiki: Requires State Info 46\nUsed when enemies are fighting multiple targets.\nPositive values increase chance to be targeted, negative values decrease chance.

sightSearchEnemyCut.Wiki: Requires State Info 8\nMakes it harder for enemies to see you.

hearingSearchEnemyCut.Wiki: Requires State Info 54\nMakes it harder for enemies to hear you.

soulStealRate.Wiki: Likely non functional. Apparently related to a Soul Steal ability (Demon's Souls Souldrain?)

lifeReductionRate.Wiki: Multiplier applied to the duration of the effect specified in lifeReductionType/Effect Duration - State Info.

hpRecoverRate.Wiki: Multiplier applied to any increase in character's current HP.\nDoes not affect Estus healing.

atkOccurenceSpEffectId.Wiki: Player - Requires State Info 153\nEnemies - Requires State Info 152

spCategory.Wiki: Determines spEffect behavior such as with other spEffects or itself.

categoryPriority.Wiki: Priority ordering for special effect to be applied on each update (lower values are updated first).

saveCategory.Wiki: Determines automatic game saving behavior (used for status ailments primarily). Set to -1 for no saving.

changeMagicSlot.Wiki: Adds or removes attunement slots, may cause crashing if total slots goes above 14.

changeMiracleSlot.Wiki: Likely non functional, holdover from Demon's Souls.

heroPointDamage.Wiki: Values from 1-99 subtract Humanity, values from 255-156 add Humanity going down (255 = +1, 254 = +2, etc)

flickDamageCutRate.Wiki: How much to reduce damage of flicked attacks.

atkAttribute.Wiki: Can change the physical damage type done by attacks.

spAttribute.Wiki: Determines visual effects of hits for buffs.

wepParamChange.Wiki: Value 3: Used by status effects and spell boosts\nValue 4: Affects attacks with behavior category 9.

lifeReductionType.Wiki: Type of effect whose duration is affected by Effect Duration Multiplier.

useSpEffectEffect.Wiki: Use visual effect from State Info Visuals table

bAdjustMagicAbility.Wiki: Scales certain fields based on spell buff derived from current INT.

bAdjustFaithAbility.Wiki: Scales certain fields based on spell buff derived from current FTH.

bGameClearBonus.Wiki: Enables the effect if in NG+

bCurrHPIndependeMaxHP.Wiki: Used for max HP reduction effects to keep health at lowered amount when effect is removed.

enableCharm.Wiki: Allows being affected by Rapport and other charm effects.

isExtendSpEffectLife.Wiki: Causes spEffect to have duration adjustable by effects like Lingering Dragoncrest Ring.

disableFrost.Wiki: Scales certain fields based on spell buff derived from current STR.

chargeAttackParamChange.Wiki: Scales certain fields based on spell buff derived from current DEX.

Unk15.Wiki: Affects AI's likelyhood of attacking when fighting in a group.

physRate.Wiki: Affects damage done to Demon type enemies.

magicRate.Wiki: Affects damage done to Undead type enemies.\nValues above 1 prevent resurrection.

fireRate.Wiki: Affects damage done to Hollow type enemies.

thunderRate.Wiki: Affects damage done to Abyss type enemies.

darkRate.Wiki: Affects damage done to WeakE type enemies.

staminaRate.Wiki: Affects damage done to WeakF type enemies.
